    "body": "> Another idea we've been thinking about is switching to a single version for our monorepo packages\r\n\r\nJust to follow up on the discussion in Discourse, switching from independent package versions to lockstep versioning might make the release process easier.\r\n\r\nWhenever you publish with lerna, each package that has changed within the monorepo will be bumped to the selected version and, if one of the packages within the monorepo depends on one of the packages getting bumped and published, that package will also be bumped and published.\r\n\r\nKeep in mind each package that is published will be tagged with the same version number, so you would have to start with whatever the next version is for the package with the latest version in the monorepo.",
